602016-04-29
ELECTRONIC ORDER: Defendants have filed an Emergency Motion to Compel the Production of Documents 59 . After reviewing the motion, the Court determines that the following expedited briefing schedule is most appropriate to facilitate this motion's prompt and efficient disposition. Plaintiffs must file a written response by 9:00 a.m. Central on May 2, 2016. The response should include a detailed affidavit or affidavits (or declarations) or other evidence to fully enable the Court to determine whether the documents that Defendants challenge are protected work product or attorney-client privileged communications as to which the privilege and/or protection have not been waived, including (without revealing any protected work product or privileged information) a detailed description of the documents in dispute and a statement of specific and precise reasons for Plaintiffs' claim of protection from disclosure as to each document based on the governing standards. Plaintiffs must be prepared on Monday, May 2, 2016 to provide the challenged documents to the Court for in camera review if -- but only if -- the Court so requests after reviewing the response. Unless the Court informs the parties otherwise, the Court will rule on the motion without a hearing, oral argument, or reply. Plaintiffs should be prepared to produce any documents or electronically stored information at issue in the motion by as early as the morning of May 3, 2016 if the Court grants the motion in whole or in part. (Ordered by Magistrate Judge David L. Horan on 4/29/2016.) (Entered: 04/29/2016)
