1132017-01-09
Opinion of USCA in accordance with USCA judgment re 84 Notice of Appeal. This appeal relates only to the injunctive relief the parties sought concerning the election that was set to take place at the 6/10/2016 annual meeting. As that event has now occurred, this appeal of the district court's ruling on the requests for injunctive relief does not present a live controversy. The appeal is DISMISSED as moot. (axm) (Entered: 01/09/2017)
1142017-01-09
JUDGMENT/MANDATE of USCA as to 84 Notice of Appeal. The appeal is dismissed as moot. Issued as Mandate: 1/9/2017. (axm) (Entered: 01/09/2017)
1152017-01-12
USCA5 Bill of Cost. (axm) (Entered: 01/13/2017)
1162017-01-13
***PLEASE DISREGARD - Duplicate entry of document 115 *** USCA5 Bill of Cost. (axm) Modified on 1/13/2017 (axm). (Entered: 01/13/2017)
1172017-01-18
REPLY filed by Sessa Capital (Master) LP re: 110 MOTION for Sanctions (Attachments: # 1 Appendix 63-83) (Skiermont, Paul) (Entered: 01/18/2017)
1182017-02-17
ORDER: The Court grants in part and denies in part Sessa's motion to dismiss plaintiffs' amended complaint, grants the motions to dismiss Counts IV of Sessa's first amended counterclaims and third-party claims, denies Sessa's motion for leave to file a surreply, grants the motion to consolidate related cases, grants Ashford Prime's motion to compel, and denies the motions for sanctions. Ashford I is hereby consolidated with Ashford II. All pleadings, motions, or other papers from this point forward will be filed in Civil Action No. 3:16-CV-00527-N. The clerk of court shall administratively close 3:16-CV-00713-N for statistical purposes. (Ordered by Judge David C Godbey on 2/17/2017) (sss) (Entered: 02/17/2017)
1192017-02-24
AGREED ORDER FOR RELEASE OF PRELIMINARY INJUNCTION BOND: The Court hereby ORDERS that the Bond and accrued interest be released to Ashford Hospitality Prime and directs the Clerk of the Court to release the Bond to Ashford Hospitality Prime and mail the check to Andrews Kurth Kenyon LLP, 1717 Main Street, Suite 3700, Dallas, Texas 75201, Attn: Debbie Reese. (Ordered by Judge David C Godbey on 2/24/2017) (sss) (Entered: 02/24/2017)

  


















